metadata.dc:description: A case of an asymptomatic 9-year-old girl is reported. She was diagnosed of aortic regurgitation by valvular prolapse without other systemic or valvular pathology associated. We discuss her etiology and physiopathology.
metadata.dc:title: Insuficiencia aórtica en niña asintomática: prolapso valvular como único hallazgo.
[Aortic insufficiency in an asymptomatic girl: valve prolapse as the only finding].
